<L>Whoever will, let come to this full fount,</L>
<L>And drink to thir&s;t no more! Eat, O my friends,</L>
<L>The bread of life; who eat &s;hall never die!</L>
<L>My &s;oul on wings of love &s;eraphic flies,</L>
<L>Makes ha&s;te under the &s;hadow of life's tree</L>
<L>To &s;it, with great delight; tho&s;e delicates</L>
<L>To ta&s;te, as angels food to &s;ouls as &s;weet!</L>
<L>Burns then my heart with ardour too inten&s;e,</L>
<L><HI>Enthu&s;ia&s;tic or delu&s;ion this?</HI></L>
